<div class = 'img'><a href = 'http://martinfowler.com/articles/testing-culture.html#heartbleed'><img src = 'http://martinfowler.com/articles/testing-culture/msb.jpg' width = '70px;' height = '' alt = '' title = ''/></a></div><p>In this second installment <a href="https://plus.google.com/+MikeBland/posts">Mike Bland</a> takes <a href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/testing-culture.html">a look at the Heartbleed bug</a>, showing what kind of unit tests would expose the bug and the testing culture that would encourage these tests to be written. He further stresses that a testing culture wouldn’t consider a bug to be fixed without additional tests and posits a corollary to Linus’s Law.</p>
